## Query

Query services are provided via a GET HTTPS interface that produces JSON objects. It is RECOMMENDED that the DIMEs Authorization certificate is used in HTTPS for server side authentication. Client SHOULD use their Operational certificate as part of client side of the HTTPS exchange. 

DIMEs MUST use the `/.well-known/ome/query/` endpoint for interoperable client discovery. See REF.HME.IFACES for implementation details.

### Uniform Resource Identifier {#query-uri}

The DIMEs Issuing certificate MUST contain the base portion of the URI as described in DKIX. Clients obtain the base URI of a given DET by performing the recursive lookup to obtain the Issuing certificate. A DIME MAY place the base URI in Operational certificates, enabling a single lookup to obtain the base URI, but clients MUST NOT depend on this behavior.

Clients MUST construct the full query string by concatenating the base URI from a certificate and the `/.well-known/ome/query/<ipv6>` of the desired DET before performing the HTTPS GET call. 

